We then went to another vet and they looked at it took some cells and looked under the microscope and no cancer just a hystiocytoma. Google it.

Boxers are prone to get these. Something a vet should know right away. Needless to say it cost only $200. To have this done. How can a company that treats animals want to rip off family's? They made us feel awful cuz we couldn't afford the $2500. Please do not take ur pet here. Only in it for money and want to RIP u off.
